		<Title>Microsoft Meltdown and Spectre Detection Results - Windows</Title>
		<Description><![CDATA[<P>This Analysis reports on Microsoft suggested actions for the Meltdown and Spectre vulnerabilities. It requires that you first run a powershell script created by Microsoft and made available in the&nbsp;"Run Microsoft Meltdown and Spectre Detection Tool - Windows" that is paired with this Analysis.</P>
<P>Microsoft has made more information on the suggestions recommended here at the following links for servers ( <A href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4072698/windows-server-guidance-to-protect-against-the-speculative-execution">https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4072698/windows-server-guidance-to-protect-against-the-speculative-execution</A> ) and workstations ( <A href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4073119/windows-client-guidance-for-it-pros-to-protect-against-speculative-exe">https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4073119/windows-client-guidance-for-it-pros-to-protect-against-speculative-exe</A> ).</P>
<P><STRONG>BIOS/Firmware update suggested:</STRONG> Microsoft suggests that you install BIOS/firmware updates for machines that report true to this. <BR><STRONG>Windows OS Update suggested:</STRONG> Microsoft suggests you install the latests Windows updates with support for speculation control mitigation if devices return true for this property. <BR><STRONG>Additional Configurations suggested:</STRONG> Microsoft suggests that you follow additional recommendations at the following link for any devices that report true to this property: <A href="https://support.microsoft.com/help/4072698">https://support.microsoft.com/help/4072698</A></P>]]></Description>
